<subSubSection pageNumber="657" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="657">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">Note:</emphasis>
Lacaita (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">J. Linn. Soc., Bot.</emphasis>
47: 155-159. 1925) observed that this name had been in use for the taxon subsequently known as 
<taxonomicName authority="Desr." authorityName="Desr." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Marrubium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">M. incanum</emphasis>
Desr.
</taxonomicName>
, but that the two Clifford sheets (illustrated by him as f. 2 and 3) are identifiable as 
<taxonomicName authority="Montbr. &amp; Auch. He" authorityName="Montbr. &amp; Auch. He" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Marrubium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="globosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">M. globosum</emphasis>
Montbr. &amp; Auch. He
</taxonomicName>
identified 
<specimenReference collectionCode="LINN" specimenCode="738.3">
Herb. Linn. 738.3 (
<collectionCode>LINN</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
as a mixture of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Marrubium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">M. incanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Marrubium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="supinum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">M. supinum</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, with sheet 738.4 (LINN) a further mixture of a species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Marrubium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">Marrubium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Sideritis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="syriaca">Sideritis syriaca</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Lacaita did not formally choose a type for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Marrubium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="candidissimum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">M. candidissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has been associated with a number of different species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Marrubium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">Marrubium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at one time or another. As a result of this confusion, the name has fallen out of use in recent years. Typification of this name using any of the available 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Marrubium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">Marrubium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
elements could have displaced one of the now established later names, and caused considerable confusion. Turland therefore typified the name using the specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Sideritis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="syriaca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">S. syriaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, supported by an 
<typeStatus>epitype</typeStatus>
, allowing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Marrubium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="candidissimum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">M. candidissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to fall into its synonymy.
</paragraph>
